    "narrative": "The **Gunnar Henderson** matchup against Houser stands as our clear centerpiece today, anchoring the lineup with a robust 83.29 efficiency score. The combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park and Houser\u2019s questionable xERA provides the perfect runway for him to anchor our R/HR production. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.87) and **Marcell Ozuna** (66.40) represent elite-tier starts; **Marcell Ozuna** benefits significantly from a 10% boost due to favorable wind conditions against Taillon, while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** maintains a high floor thanks to a solid 0.384 xwOBA. We are also looking for **Miguel Vargas** to capitalize on a +10% order adjustment and wind-aided hitting environment at the top of the order, pushing his score to a very respectable 63.64.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved choosing between the marginal outputs of **Jorge Polanco** (58.80) and **Josh Jung** (57.03). Ultimately, **Jorge Polanco** earned the nod primarily due to his confirmed lineup placement; the risk associated with **Josh Jung** hitting in the 8-hole against a tricky arm like Sasaki proved too significant to ignore. Elsewhere, we are proceeding with caution regarding **Jackson Merrill**; while his 58.07 score is respectable, the 39% rain risk hanging over his contest against Freeland necessitates a close watch as first pitch approaches. Despite the daunting matchup against deGrom, we are maintaining **Kyle Tucker** and **Andy Pages** in the OF slots, as their underlying projection metrics hold up better than the bench alternatives, even after adjusting for the elite skill of the opposing pitcher.",
